import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import geopandas as gpd
from mpl_toolkits.axes_grid1 import make_axes_locatable

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    # Load US states shapefile
    us_states = gpd.read_file("https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PublicaMundi/MappingAPI/master/data/geojson/us-states.json")

    # Count airports per state
    airport_counts = data['state'].value_counts().reset_index()
    airport_counts.columns = ['state', 'count']

    # Merge airport counts with states shapefile
    us_states = us_states.merge(airport_counts, left_on='id', right_on='state', how='left')

    # Plot choropleth map
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(1, 1, figsize=(15, 25))
    divider = make_axes_locatable(ax)
    cax = divider.append_axes("right", size="5%", pad=0.1)
    us_states.plot(column='count', cmap='coolwarm', linewidth=0.8, ax=ax, edgecolor='0.8', legend=True, cax=cax)

    # Set title and legend
    plt.title("What is the distribution of airports across different states in the US?", wrap=True)
    ax.set_axis_off()

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    city_airport_counts = data['city'].value_counts().head(10)
    city_airport_counts = city_airport_counts.reset_index()
    city_airport_counts.columns = ['city', 'count']

    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.barplot(x='city', y='count', data=city_airport_counts, palette='viridis')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of airports across different cities in the US?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('City')
    plt.ylabel('Number of Airports')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend(city_airport_counts['city'], title='Cities', loc='upper right')

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    # Define airport size categories
    def categorize_airport_size(row):
        if row['latitude'] < 30:
            return 'Small'
        elif row['latitude'] < 45:
            return 'Medium'
        else:
            return 'Large'

    data['airport_size'] = data.apply(categorize_airport_size, axis=1)

    # Plot the histogram
    ax = sns.histplot(data=data, x='airport_size', discrete=True, palette='viridis')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of airport sizes in the US?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Airport Size')
    plt.ylabel('Number of Airports')
    plt.legend(title='Airport Sizes', labels=['Small', 'Medium', 'Large'], loc='upper right')

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
